<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; TROJANS INSPIRED BY LOSS TO OREGON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach John Robinson, on the turnaround his team has made, having won five 
straight since a 22-7 loss to Oregon Oct. 1: 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a combination of our young players getting game experience and everyone 
making maximum efforts on every play. When everyone has a maximum effort on 
every play. . . . That's what causes big plays." 
</P>
<P>
 Said Keith Burns, who coaches the safeties: "A lot of guys got mad after that 
Oregon loss. We noticed . . . seven or eight guys were just flying through the 
air out here (in practice). 
</P>
<P>
 "Then after the Oregon State game, it was nine or 10 guys. After Stanford, it 
was 13 or 14. Now, just about everyone is playing hard in practice and the 
games." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Wide receiver Keyshawn Johnson ranks fifth in Pacific 10 Conference receiving 
statistics only because the rankings are pegged to catches per game. But 
Johnson is first in average yards per catch, 20.8. Of his 41 catches, 36 have 
been for first downs. He has had five consecutive 100-yard games. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Rob Johnson is the Trojans' only conference statistical leader, 
with a 157.20 pass efficiency rating. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
