COLLEGE BASKETBALL / PRESEASON NIT; USF AND MEMPHIS GET VICTORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gerald Walker scored 24 points and San Francisco used a 12-0 run at the start 
of the second half Thursday to beat New Mexico, 80-74, in the first round of 
the Preseason NIT at Albuquerque, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons advanced to the quarterfinals at Memphis, Tenn., where Memphis also 
was a winner Thursday, beating Southwestern Louisiana, 70-66. 
</P>
<P>
 New Mexico led, 38-37, at halftime, but the Dons built an 11-point lead in the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
 At Memphis, the Tigers, who trailed by as many as 16 in the first half, used a 
27-6 run in building a 67-58 lead with 4:12 to play. David Vaughn had 17 points 
and 13 rebounds for the Tigers. 
</P>
