<P>
 British Petroleum to Pay $1.4 Billion to Alaska: The payment by British 
Petroleum's Alaska unit will resolve state tax disputes that date back to the 
time when oil began flowing through the trans-Alaska pipeline, Alaska Gov. 
Walter Hickel said. The settlement, coming after years of negotiations, is the 
largest Alaska tax deal ever, Hickel said at a news conference. Paul Laird, 
spokesman for BP's Alaska unit, said the payments will not have a material 
effect on the company's financial results or operations. 
