<TEXT>
<P>
 Joseph Boucher has been appointed president of Santa Ana-based Cybernetics 
Products Inc.'s newly acquired Computer Services of America division.Before 
joining the company, he was senior technical business group site operations 
manager for Digital Equipment Corp.  
</P>
<P>
 Bob Vohs has been appointed president and chief operating officer of Cost Care 
Inc., a Newport Beach managed health-care company. He succeeds Virginia Cirica, 
who is retiring in December. Vohs was previously a health care consultant in 
Wichita, Kan., and also worked at Equicor and Cigna. Before entering the 
health-care field, he was a practicing attorney. In addition, Larry Goelman, 
chief executive of Cost Care, has been appointed chairman. He succeeds William 
E. Caulfield, who remains as chairman of the executive committee. 
