<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; DEADLINE NEARS FOR SCHOOL TRANSFERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Parents in the Oxnard Union High School District who want to take advantage of 
a new state law on school choice have until Wednesday to apply to transfer 
students to a different school within the district. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the law, which took effect early this year, school officials must allow 
students to transfer to any school in the district. 
</P>
<P>
 But the school must have room for additional students and the transfers must 
not cause major shifts in the school's racial balance. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of crowding in the Oxnard district, some of the five high schools have 
only limited space for transfers. 
</P>
<P>
 Interested parents should call the district office at 385-2500, or visit one 
of the school offices to get a brochure explaining the transfer process. MAIA 
DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
