<P>
2 MEN HELD AFTER YOUTHS FIRED UPON IN SIMI VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men suspected of shooting at a group of Simi Valley youths were in custody 
Thursday at Ventura County Jail, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mauricio Donoso, 19, and Cory Pohlmeier, 20, both of Simi Valley, were 
arrested earlier this week, Sheriff's Lt. Mark Layhew said. 
</P>
<P>
 A third suspect was arrested, but was released after questioning, Layhew said. 
Investigators believe a fourth man was involved in the incident but have not 
identified him, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the shooting, which occurred at 3:28 a.m. Sunday, Layhew 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Herman Mathis Smith, 18, of Simi Valley was sitting in a car in the 1800 block 
of Charing Court with two juveniles from Simi Valley when the suspects walked 
up to the vehicle, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Donoso allegedly pulled a handgun and fired at the youths in the car, police 
said. The window shattered, but no one was hurt, Layhew said. 
</P>
<P>
 Pohlmeier hurled a bottle at the car as the suspects fled on foot, police 
said. 
</P>
