<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NHL'S TROUBLED SEASON SHRINKS YET AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN, From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The NHL's fast-shrinking schedule was reduced for the third time during the 
owners' lockout as the league canceled 10 more games per team Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The widely expected move means the number of games canceled for each team has 
reached 24.The breakdown of lost games is 11 home, 11 road and two at neutral 
sites. As in previous cancellations, the league made no announcement as to 
which games will be canceled, saying the revised schedule will be released if 
and when the season begins. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, the NHL and the players' union met for seven hours in Boston and 
plan to negotiate again today. It is the first time since Oct. 4-5 that the 
parties have negotiated on consecutive days. Neither side would comment on 
Thursday's discussions. LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
