<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After losing to Boris Becker in his opener, Pete Sampras rallied to beat 
Stefan Edberg, 4-6, 6-3, 7-6 (7-3) and stay alive at the IBM/ATP Tour World 
Championship at Frankfurt, Germany. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Hall of Fame right-hander Ferguson Jenkins has been hired by the Cubs as their 
pitching coach. They also hired Florida Marlin scout John Young as a special 
assistant to General Manager Ed Lynch. 
</P>
