predicting such results immediately for Fullerton but he is determined to make 
the Indians into a playoff contender. "Our goal is to be the most fundamentally 
sound team out there," Fair said. "If we are that, the wins will come." Fair 
goes on to praise his club's intelligence and desire; whether they can 
compensate for Fullerton's lack of overall height is the big question. Another 
question is how quickly expected leaders Schatz (9.4 points) and Young (3.0) 
fit in once the football season ends. But Fair is undaunted. "This is a school 
