<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK; FERRARA EQUALS TRACK RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ferrara, a colt bred by the late Don Ameche and now racing for the actor's 
son, Don Ameche Jr., has raced twice since returning from an injury, and the 
results have been fast and faster. 
</P>
<P>
 On Oct. 22, Ferrara ran six furlongs in 1:08 3/5 at Santa Anita, and on 
Thursday he won by three lengths over Isitingood at Hollywood Park, tying the 
track record for 6 1/2 furlongs with a clocking of 1:13 4/5. 
</P>
<P>
 Ferrara was a promising 2-year-old for trainer Gary Jones a year ago, running 
third in the Del Mar Futurity and the Norfolk at Santa Anita, but he cracked a 
bone in a hind leg early this year. Ferrara scored his victory at Santa Anita, 
by a half-length, also over Isitingood, in his first start in almost 10 months. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden again Thursday by Chris Antley, Ferrara took the lead on the turn and 
hit the wire in the same time that Arches Of Gold posted in setting the track 
record in 1992. Ferrara paid $6.20 as the second choice. 
</P>
<P>
 Alex Solis was unseated by his mount, Make Your Call, at the start of the 
third race. The jockey suffered a cut on his left hand and took off the rest of 
his mounts after complaining of dizziness. BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111894-0127 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 099787 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
November 18, 1994, Friday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 8; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
