<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: EXPOS NAME BENEDICT TO MINOR LEAGUE PITCHING POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Chatsworth High and Valley College baseball player Jim Benedict has 
been named minor league pitching coordinator for the Montreal Expos. 
</P>
<P>
 Benedict, 33, succeeds Herm Starrette, who is now the pitching coach for the 
Boston Red Sox. 
</P>
<P>
 Benedict, who for the last four years worked as a scout for the Texas Rangers, 
pitched three seasons in the Kansas City Royal and Atlanta Brave organizations, 
advancing to the double-A level. 
</P>
<P>
 The budget-conscious Expos traditionally have relied on younger players 
brought up through their own system. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's the intriguing part of this job," Benedict said. "We have good young 
pitching and we build from within." 
</P>
<P>
 Benedict has also coached at Valley College, Loyola Marymount and Chapman. 
DAVE DESMOND 
