<TEXT>
<P>
 Birmingham High football Coach Chick Epstein said he will resign after 17 
years as the Braves' mentor at the conclusion of the City Section 3-A Division 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's been great," said Epstein, 52. "It's a noble profession, but I wanted a 
chance to enjoy my home life and my family. I'll let somebody young take over." 
</P>
<P>
 Epstein will continue to teach and coach golf at the Van Nuys school.  
</P>
<P>
 The Braves, who play a first-round playoff game tonight at Reseda, earned 
playoff berths six times during Epstein's tenure. His career record there was 
75-82-4. KENNEDY COSGROVE 
