want to get to the next step. These seniors have been on varsity for three 
years. They think this can be a special year." Murphy is playing a pat hand, 
but it's a full house led by Clark. The Raiders can play it any way you 
want--big, small, uptempo, half-court--and play it better than most. Since they 
tower over the rest of the Freeway League heightwise, Murphy's biggest problem 
may be to keep Sonora motivated until the playoffs. "I think our league is 
really balanced; everybody is pretty good," Murphy said. Perhaps, but there 
isn't a Freeway coach who wouldn't swap teams with Murphy if he had the chance. 
