<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LONG BEACH; CITY 
COUNCILMAN TO SEEK DANA'S SUPERVISORIAL POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Douglas S. Drummond, a Long Beach city councilman since 1990 and currently 
vice mayor, announced Thursday that he will run for the 4th District 
supervisorial seat to be vacated by Deane Dana. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana, a supervisor for 16 years, announced this week that he will retire when 
his term expires in 1996 and endorsed his chief deputy, Don Knabe, to be his 
successor. 
</P>
<P>
 Drummond said he set his sights on the supervisor's seat because he has 
enjoyed public service and because problems in the county pose "serious 
challenges." 
</P>
<P>
 "The county has not done a very good job of economizing; they have not made 
enough cutbacks to deal with economic realities," Drummond said. 
</P>
<P>
 Drummond, 57, was in the Long Beach Police Department 29 years before retiring 
at the rank of commander in 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
