<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: PASADENA; CITY FIRE 
CHIEF PEKEROL SUSPENDED WITH PAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena Fire Chief Kaya Pekerol, who was appointed in 1981, has been 
suspended with pay by City Manager Philip A. Hawkey. 
</P>
<P>
 City spokeswoman Ann Erdman announced the suspension Tuesday but declined to 
give details because it is a personnel matter. Hawkey is to meet Tuesday with 
Pekerol to determine whether further action will be taken, Erdman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Pekerol was the target of criticism this year when his department was cited by 
state safety officials for failing to provide firefighters with protective 
shields, among other things. 
