<P>
 Matsushita Relocating Facility to San Diego: Matsushita Television Co. of 
Japan will move its Franklin Park, Ill., headquarters office for North American 
research and engineering early next year. Matsushita's move to the new 
110,000-square-foot facility in the Otay Mesa area near the U.S.-Mexico border 
will bring 120 high-paying jobs to San Diego, city officials said.The Japanese 
consumer electronics giant has several TV plants employing 3,000 workers in 
Tijuana, where it primarily manufactures Panasonic sets. The company, which had 
announced earlier that it was looking at sites in Southern California, said it 
was attracted by San Diego's strategic location for Latin American and Pacfic 
Rim trade and by financial incentives -- mainly fee waivers -- valued by Mayor 
Susan Golding at about $150,000. 
