BRIEFLY: INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lloyd's Will Reportedly Increase Names Offer: Insurer Lloyd's of London plans 
to offer $1.7 billion to loss-strapped investors in an effort to halt 
litigation, the Guardian newspaper reported today in London. "It is understood 
that the ruling council of Lloyd's will discuss the offer at its monthly 
meeting in early December," the newspaper said. If the deal is approved, an 
offer could be made before Christmas to the 22,000 "names," the people who 
support the insurance market with their personal wealth. 
</P>
