<P>
 Hewlett-Packard Profit Up 60%: A 25% increase in orders led to the 
fourth-quarter gain, the Palo Alto-based company said.Hewlett-Packard Co. 
earned $476 million, or $1.83 a share, for the three months ended Oct. 31. The 
company had earnings of $298 million, or $1.18 a share, for the comparable 
period last year. Revenue for the quarter was $7 billion, a 23% increase over 
the 1993 period. 
