BRIEFLY: AIRLINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crash Fallout Continues to Hurt USAir: More than two months after its latest 
plane crash, the airline continues to lose ticket sales from worried fliers and 
says its fourth-quarter results will be hurt significantly.Passenger traffic 
has been depressed to the point where fare discounts can't attract enough new 
passengers to offset price cuts, USAir said in a quarterly filing with the 
Securities and Exchange Commission. USAir spokeswoman Andrea Butler said that, 
based on advance bookings, a full recovery isn't expected until January. Two 
USAir crashes this year raised doubts among some travelers about the carrier's 
safety. 
</P>
