CONSUMER BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New Alcohol-Free Beer: Brewing giant Anheuser-Busch Inc. introduced a new 
nonalcoholic brew, Busch NA, in selected markets this week.It should be 
available nationwide within the first few months of 1995. Busch NA is brewed 
with the same ingredients as Busch and Busch Light, but the alcohol is removed 
through an evaporation process at the end of the brewing cycle. Busch NA 
contains less than 0.5% alcohol by volume, the maximum allowed by the 
government for this product category, said St. Louis-based Anheuser-Busch, the 
world's largest brewer. 
</P>
