<TEXT>
<P>
 Cosmetics Line Expanding: Maybelline Inc. said this week that it will 
introduce seven products in February, including two in its Revitalizing line 
for women 35 and older. Robert Hiatt, president and chief executive, said 
Maybelline is trying to "accelerate the 'class to mass' trend in cosmetics, as 
more consumers turn away from higher-priced department store brands for the 
convenience and affordability of high-quality mass-market products."The 
products include mascara, an oil-free cream foundation, eye shadow, eyeliner 
and blush. Maybelline said the two products in its Revitalizing line are 
Revitalizing Alpha Hydroxy Make-Up and Revitalizing Alpha Hydroxy Intensive 
Night Cream. Sales of the Revitalizing line of cosmetics and skin care, which 
was launched in February, have been slower than expected both by analysts and 
the company. Memphis, Tenn.-based Maybelline sells its products in most 
drugstores, discount stores, supermarkets and cosmetics stores. 
