<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONSUMER BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Year-End Score Card: The Federal Trade Commission said this week that its 
antitrust unit has brought 33 enforcement actions against alleged 
anti-competitive corporate behavior in the past year, the most since 1980. It 
also said its consumer protection unit was the most active it has been in 
years, bringing 233 actions for fraud and other matters in the fiscal year 
ended Sept. 30.The FTC said that of the 33 antitrust cases, 20 involved 
allegedly anti-competitive mergers in industries including drugs, defense, 
telecommunications, financial services and consumer goods. The other 13 
involved allegedly anti-competitive behavior by, among others, medical 
professionals, automobile dealers and cable television systems, the FTC said. 
On the consumer side, the agency said it focused on consumer scams that 
involved emerging technologies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
