<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended Nov. 13, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units sold:  
</P>
<P>
 Latest week: Albums: 12.0 Singles: 2.0 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago: Albums: 10.9 Singles: 1.8 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago: Albums: 11.1 Singles: 2.3 Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 Amid all the turmoil in the executive ranks of the music industry, Columbia 
Records Group Chairman Don Ienner has been dramatically changing the look of 
his leadership team. Ienner recently named former Virgin U.S. heads Jeff 
Ayeroff and Jordan Harris to head a new West Coast label for Columbia, 
following the collapse of the duo's impending deal at the rapidly changing 
Warner Bros.Ienner has also hired former Elektra executive Jon Leshay for an 
East Coast senior marketing post, with emphasis on alternative music, while 
former Geffen A&R man John David Kalodner will join the label in a similar post 
on the West Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Hits magazine is a weekly music industry trade publication. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Soundscan Inc. 
</P>
