<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SYLMAR; EYE CARE FIRM AIDS ABUSED CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lens Crafters will provide free eye care, prescriptions and glasses for 48 
abused and neglected children who reside at the Hathaway Children's Services 
residential campus in Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 The gift is part of an annual charitable program that targets needy children 
in Southern California communities.The eye care and glasses will be 
administered at Lens Crafters locations in Northridge and Sherman Oaks.  
</P>
<P>
 "This gift is a tremendous help to us," said Peggi Preston, development 
associate for Hathaway Children's Services, located on a 300-acre residential 
campus. 
</P>
<P>
 The campus is home to 120 children, ages 5 to 18. Cecil B. DeMille once owned 
this land that overlooks the San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our children are all wards of the court who've been removed from their 
homes," Preston said. "They've been sexually abused, physically abused and, in 
many cases, simply abandoned. Most of them have never had the money to afford 
proper eye care." 
</P>
<P>
 Preston said Hathaway children have a continuous need for donations of health 
services, including eye care and corrective lenses. 
</P>
<P>
 For further information, contact Preston at (818) 896-2474. TIM MAY 
</P>
