<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; CRASH KILLS WOMAN, 25, INJURES SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 25-year-old woman was killed and her 18-month-old son slightly injured 
Thursday when the vehicle in which they were riding veered off the road and 
flipped over in a remote desert area east of Lancaster, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lonnie Hauser of Palmdale was driving north on 150th Street East, near Avenue 
J about 9:30 a.m. when her 1978 Jeep drifted onto the right shoulder, 
California Highway Patrol Officer Miguel Siordia said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman turned sharply to the left to get back on the road, but the vehicle 
continued across the roadway to the opposite side and flipped over, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jeep's removable hardtop came off and Hauser was thrown out of the vehicle 
even though she was wearing a lap belt, the officer said. Her son, Kurt Hauser, 
was secured in a child seat and remained in the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
 The mother and son were taken by helicopter to Antelope Valley Hospital, where 
Hauser died at 11:07 a.m., Siordia said. Her son was treated for bruises and 
scrapes but was not seriously injured, the officer said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
