<HEADLINE>
<P>
REDDING BOMB SCARE FORCES 2,000 TO FLEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 2,000 people were evacuated from their homes and offices Thursday after 
authorities found a possible bomb attached to two large propane tanks. 
</P>
<P>
 Bomb squad members removed the device and rendered it safe at about 6:30 p.m., 
said Lt. Herb Davidson of the Shasta County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators planned to dismantle the bomb, which appeared to be a "genuine 
explosive device," Davidson said. Authorities would not describe it. 
</P>
<P>
 The device caused concern because it was attached to the propane tanks and an 
explosion could have devastated everything for several blocks, said Sheriff's 
Sgt. Arlin Markin. 
</P>
<P>
 All homes and businesses within a one-mile radius of the industrial area south 
of downtown were evacuated after authorities discovered the bomb Thursday 
morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Those evacuated were allowed to return Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities discovered the device after an anonymous caller directed deputies 
to the site shortly after 8 a.m. 
</P>
