<TEXT>
<P>
 Thrift's New Headquarters: Household Bank, a savings and loan that operates in 
seven states, has moved its main office and western division headquarters from 
Newport Beach to Irvine. The thrift, a subsidiary of Household International 
Inc., is chartered in California but is operated out of the parent company's 
headquarters in Chicago. The thrift is Orange County's second-largest thrift 
and the nation's 14th-largest S&L with $8.6 billion in loans and other assets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
