COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; EXTRA GUARD ASSIGNED TO BUSY CROSSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An additional crossing guard will be assigned to an intersection used by 
students at Bernardo Yorba Middle School and Fairmont Elementary School, the 
City Council decided this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently, the city has one crossing guard to help students cross Fairmont 
Boulevard and Old Ranch Road. 
</P>
<P>
 A recent study of pedestrian traffic in the area showed that more than 450 
students cross one or both of those streets in the morning and afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents of students at both schools have frequently requested that another 
crossing guard be assigned to the area. DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
