</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Highway Patrol has scheduled two officer recruitment seminars 
in Orange County.The seminars are scheduled for 9 to 11 a.m. Saturday and 6 to 
8 p.m. Tuesday at the Highway Patrol office in Westminster, 13200 Golden West 
St. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants must be 20 to 31 and have a high school diploma or the equivalent. 
Recruits also must pass written, physical and psychological tests and undergo a 
background investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 Successful candidates will receive a salary of at least $2,658 per month while 
attending the California Highway Patrol Academy in Sacramento. 
</P>
