<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Plans for a roller hockey arena at the Wardlow School were shot down Thursday 
night by the school board, after neighbors predicted the arena would bring 
traffic and noise.  
</P>
<P>
 The Fountain Valley school board refused to waive its policy that prohibits 
roller sports on school grounds -- even a vacant school site such as Wardlow. 
</P>
<P>
 The city of Huntington Beach and Kid Connection, a nonprofit youth group, had 
proposed the arena at the school at 9191 Pioneer Drive om Huntington Beach, and 
that city had approved spending $5,000 to help build it. 
</P>
<P>
 But Trustee Catherine Hacker, who lives near the school, called it a "bad 
idea." 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm worried about the liability issue, and as a board member we have a fiscal 
responsibility. I was also concerned that there was no neighborhood support for 
it. The site was not a good site for a roller hockey rink." 
</P>
