<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men doing traffic control work early Thursday at Warner Avenue and Ross 
Street were struck and injured by an unidentified motorist who fled, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Agotsch, 20, of Laguna Hills and Scott Frank, 28, of Costa Mesa were 
picking up traffic cones at 4 a.m. when they were struck by a white Toyota 
pickup, police said. 
</P>
